GPA Notes::
1. Overall GPA of 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale;
2. Combined science GPA of 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale (chemistry, biochemistry, anatomy,
physiology, etc.);
3. Grade of B (3.0 on a 4.0 scale) or better in a non-nursing Biochemistry, Physiology or
Pathophysiology course from an accredited university within the past 5 years. Graduate level is
preferred, undergraduate courses considered;
4. Grade of B (3.0 on a 4.0 scale) or better in a Statistics course from an accredited university.
Graduate level is preferred, undergraduate courses considered.
